#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Zimbabwean government has launched an online registration platform to ensure a smooth transition for citizens who will be returning home once South African exemption permits expire in June. Zimbabwe's Ambassador to South Africa David Hamadziripi says they are not sure how many would like to return. However, the South African government will ultimately decide who is permitted to enter and remain within South Africa. READ:Â Plan to assist Zimbabwe Exemption Permit holders to return home #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 Meanwhile, Zimbabwe Exemption Permit holders have welcomed their government's decision to assist citizens to return home. This comes amid uncertainty after the South African government announced that permits would not be renewed. A lawyer for some of the permit holders says legal action challenging the decision will continue. Watch the video above for more details on this story.